      • storeCertificate

        public boolean storeCertificate​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                                Certificate incert,
                                String username,
                                String password,
                                String userDN,
                                String cafp,
                                int status,
                                int type,
                                long revocationDate,
                                int revocationReason,
                                String tag,
                                int certificateProfileId,
                                long lastUpdate,
                                ExtendedInformation extendedinformation)
                         throws PublisherException
        Writes certificate to temporary file and executes an external command with the full pathname of the temporary file as argument. The temporary file is the encoded form of the certificate e.g. X.509 certificates would be encoded as ASN.1 DER. All parameters but incert are ignored.
        Specified by:
        storeCertificate in interface ICustomPublisher
        Overrides:
        storeCertificate in class CustomPublisherContainer
        Parameters:
        incert - The certificate
        username - The username
        type - The certificate type
        admin - admin
        password - Password given to the user, may be null if no password exists for the user.
        userDN - if a DN object is not found in the certificate use object from user data instead, can be null.
        cafp - Fingerprint (hex) of the CAs certificate.
        status - Status of the certificate (from CertificateDataBean.CERT_ACTIVE, CERT_REVOKED etc).
        revocationDate - Date for revocation (of revoked), like System.currentTimeMillis(), or -1 if not revoked.
        revocationReason - reason for revocation from RevokedCertInfo, RevokedCertInfo.NOT_REVOKED if not revoked.
        tag - TAg
        certificateProfileId - Profile
        lastUpdate - Date
        extendedinformation - contains extended information about the user, like picture, is null if no extendedinformation exists about the user.
        Returns:
        true if storage was successful.
        Throws:
        PublisherException - if a communication or other error occurs.
        See Also:
        ICustomPublisher.storeCertificate(org.cesecore.authentication.tokens.AuthenticationToken, java.security.cert.Certificate, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, int, int, long, int, java.lang.String, int, long, org.cesecore.certificates.endentity.ExtendedInformation)

      • storeCRL

        public boolean storeCRL​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                        byte[] incrl,
                        String cafp,
                        int number,
                        String userDN)
                 throws PublisherException
        Writes the CRL to a temporary file and executes an external command with the temporary file as argument. By default, a PublisherException is thrown if the external command returns with an errorlevel or outputs to stderr.
        Specified by:
        storeCRL in interface ICustomPublisher
        Overrides:
        storeCRL in class CustomPublisherContainer
        Parameters:
        admin - token
        incrl - The DER coded CRL to be stored.
        cafp - Fingerprint (hex) of the CAs certificate.
        number - CRL number.
        userDN - if an DN object is not found in the certificate use object from user data instead, can be null.
        Returns:
        true if storage was successful.
        Throws:
        PublisherException - if a communication or other error occurs.
        See Also:
        ICustomPublisher.storeCRL(org.cesecore.authentication.tokens.AuthenticationToken, byte[], java.lang.String, int, java.lang.String)

      • revokeCertificate

        public void revokeCertificate​(AuthenticationToken admin,
                              Certificate cert,
                              int reason)
                       throws PublisherException
        Writes certificate to temporary file and executes an external command with the full pathname of the temporary file as argument. The temporary file is the encoded form of the certificate e.g. X.509 certificates would be encoded as ASN.1 DER. All parameters but cert are ignored.
        Parameters:
        admin - Token
        cert - The certificate
        reason - Reason
        Throws:
        PublisherException - On error
